.TH ARCV "8" "juillet 2026" "Arcv 1.0.0" "System Administration Utilities"
.SH NAME
Arcv \- arcv is a lightweight, easy-to-use revision control system which keeps untouched the user's original source files and folders
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B arcv
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR]
.PP
COMMAND:
.PP
branch  BRANCH_FOLDER[:REVISION | RELEASE TAG]
.IP
Branch off a revision
.PP
check
.IP
Tell whether there are uncommitted modifications
.PP
co  [REVISION | RELEASE TAG | FILENAME[:REVISION]]
.IP
Either update current source folder with head revision (no
arguments) or checkout resp. the revision, release tag, file
from head revision to the specified output folder
.PP
diff  [(REVISION | head | current)[vs(REVISION | RELEASE TAG)]]
.IP
Make a diff with the specified revision using system diff
tool
.PP
export  [DIRECTORY]
.IP
Export to a remote Git repo
.PP
git  [(REVISION | head | current)[vs(REVISION | RELEASE TAG)]]
.IP
Make a diff with the specified revision using git
.PP
hash  [DIRECTORY]
.IP
Display the hash signature for the head revision or the
specified folder
.PP
list
.IP
List the existing source folders stored in the repository
.PP
log  [FILENAME]
.IP
Show the revision log messages from most recent to the
oldest, for the whole source or only the specified file.
.PP
meld  [(REVISION | head | current)[vs(REVISION | RELEASE TAG)]]
.IP
Make a diff with the specified revision using meld tool
.PP
pub
.IP
Creates a new release by tagging the head revision with the
content of the VERSION.txt file.
.PP
rev
.IP
Display the head revision number
.PP
tarball  [REVISION | head]
.IP
Create a tarball for the current source folder or the
specified revision
.PP
OPTIONS:
.PP
